Male genitalia
(
Figs. 6A‒E
). Uncus nearly triangular with truncated tip, constricted at the junction with tegumen; gnathos shorter than uncus, nearly pointed apically and slightly broadened at base (
Fig. 6A
); labides strongly sclerotized, club-shaped at posterior end, shorter than the length of uncus, with strongly sclerotized dense thick spines at both posterior and posterio-internal sides (
Fig. 6C
); valva elongate, with a rounded apex having a small apico-costal projection (
Fig. 6
A-a), clasper short triangular (
Fig. 6D
); juxta nearly trapezoidal with a weak depression posterio-medially; aedeagus slightly broadened near distal end, with a longitudinal dentate sclerotized plate (
Figs. 6B, E
).

Culcita with an apically rounded and broadened basally median process and four wavy elements on each side, anterior edge with a pointed sclerotized projection medially (
Fig. 6F
).
